<h2 id="conclusion">Conclusion</h2>

<p>The pigeonhole principle is a fundamental tool in mathematics that, despite its simplicity, can lead to profound and elegant solutions. Whether you‚Äôre matching socks or solving complex mathematical problems, the principle shows that sometimes, the simplest ideas can be the most powerful.</p>
